      "text": [
        ": سَأَلْتُهُ عَنِ اَلْمُعْتَكِفِ يَأْتِي أَهْلَهُ قَالَ «لاَ يَأْتِي اِمْرَأَتَهُ لَيْلاً وَ لاَ نَهَاراً وَ هُوَ مُعْتَكِفٌ »."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
          "Hadith.2107 - It is narrated by Al-Hasan ibn Al-Jahm, from Abu Al-Hasan (as), who was asked about a person performing i'tikaf engaging in relations with their spouse.\nImam (as) said: \"They must not approach their wife, neither by night nor by day, while they are in i'tikaf.\""
        ]
      }
